construction, it will be noticed, allows of the blade being set[70]
at any angle, constant or otherwise; also the pitch can be
constant or variable as desired, and any "shape" of propeller
can be fitted.

The advantage of being able to twist the blade (within
limits) on the axis is one not to be underestimated in
experimental work.



